text.tspan: Constitutes a group of behavioural competencies that focuses on Cognitive factors like
Detail Orientation, Critical thinking and Creative thinking. These cognitive competencies
are explored from the behavioural perspective. A person with strong critical thinking is
someone who is factual, systematic, evidence-based, and logical in their approach to any
task or real-life problem situation. A person with creative mindset is willing to explore
problem situations using unique and divergent approaches.
THOUGHT FACTOR

text.tspan: This Factor focuses on the competencies of the individual SELF. They are a set of
competencies that map the characteristics of an individual to the expectations of their
organisation. This factor maps to the individual’s competencies, such as being self-reliant,
having a growth mind-set, and exhibiting openness to various situations/experiences.
These are essential characteristics an individual must possess for productive functioning
in an organisation. This factor identifies elements that are present within an ideal
organisational citizen. The presence of these traits in the potential employees enables
building an effective and productive organisation.
CORE/PERSONAL FACTOR

text.data-name: This Factor focuses on your social competence, which showcases your ability to effectively handle communication and interactions with others, either individually or socially. Organisational setup usually demands teamwork and good interaction skills to e
text.tspan: This Factor focuses on your social competence, which showcases your ability to
effectively handle communication and interactions with others, either individually or
socially. Organisational setup usually demands teamwork and good interaction skills to
enhance work output and productivity. Positive social interactions set the stage for other
formal and informal interactions.
INTERPERSONAL FACTOR

text.tspan: Emotion factor deals with the individual’s ability to adjust to various situations, manage
their anxiety, be self-aware and empathetic. This factor focuses on the individual’s ability to
effectively understand and manage their emotions. It also explores how individuals can
effectively channel their emotions/feelings positively, communicate effectively, manage
relationships, and thus efficiently handle challenging situations.
EMOTION FACTOR
